{
  "text": "Compared to ad hoc home-range estimation methods such as minimum convex polygons and kernel density estimators, a key advantage of our asymptotic range estimate, which it shares with mechanistic home-range analysis [CITATION_1] , is that it is derived from a mechanistic movement model. However, our approach does not require as detailed an understanding of the behaviors defining home ranges as mechanistic home-range analysis but instead relies on identifying movement mechanisms that are consistent with the full autocorrelation structure of the data.",
